Seven-car Maglev hit a top speed of 375mph (603 km/h) during a test run near Mount Fuji . 
  It beat last week's speeds of 366mph (590kph) and beat the train's previous record of 361mph (581km/h) . 
  Maglev trains use magnets to lift the carriages above the tracks . 
  They are propelled by electrically charged magnets . 
  The train is expected to be in service in 2027 between Tokyo and Nagoya . 
 